sentences.chinese: 這個數字上的差異是不容置疑的。

sentences.english: There is little doubt that maternal-child interaction plays a very important role in child development.
sentences.chinese: 親子互動關係對子女成長的重要性，已不容置疑。
不容置疑地，我就開始戰勝他。

sentences.english: For Yadin and his contemporaries, the Bible was unassailable.
sentences.chinese: 對於雅丁和他的同代人來說，聖經是不容置疑的。

sentences.english: The indubitable evidence we produced bore down our opponents in the debate.
sentences.chinese: 我們在辯論中提出的不容置疑的證據，擊敗了對方。

sentences.english: Previous research seemed to have settled any doubts.
sentences.chinese: 對此，此前的研究結果似乎已經給出不容置疑的定論。

sentences.english: My wife has such an imperative voice that everyone coveys her.
sentences.chinese: 我老婆的意見不容置疑，人們都聽她的。

sentences.english: I mean, that’s just not disputable.
sentences.chinese: 我的意思是，那是不容置疑的。

sentences.english: Nor can I over-emphasise the importance of the WTO to Hong Kong.
sentences.chinese: 世貿對香港的重要性不容置疑。

sentences.english: Her contributions in the engineering profession over the years are indubitably remarkable.
sentences.chinese: 她多年來對工程界的貢獻，是不容置疑的。

sentences.english: The bloody events of the ongoing war would indisputably provide an answer to that speculation.
sentences.chinese: 持續不斷的血戰，將不容置疑地回答這個問題。

sentences.english: On such damning evidence the outcome of the case is beyond doubt.
sentences.chinese: 該案罪證鑿鑿，結果不容置疑。

sentences.english: Fanshen is also an unchallengeable classic.
sentences.chinese: 《翻身》也不容置疑是一部經典著作。

sentences.english: This is a fact that cannot be controverted .
sentences.chinese: 這是一個不容置疑的事實。

sentences.english: There is no doubt about what he has said.
sentences.chinese: 有關他所說的話是不容置疑的。

sentences.english: There was one insurmountable problem, however. He was bigger than me.
sentences.chinese: 這是一個不容置疑的問題，儘管他比我年紀大。
